RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILSON Q set the pace outside of a vying rival, clung to an advantage in the long duel through midstretch, edged ahead entering the final sixteenth, and held from an outer bidder. GOLD SWEEP bumped with an inner rival at the start, chased the leaders from the two path, tipped out to the five path entering the lane, rallied to offer a late bid approaching the wire but missed. WORKS FOR ME vied along the inside, prolonged the battle through midstretch, but yielded in the final sixteenth. STORMQUIST was hustled to press the top pair into the turn, but gave way entering the lane. TRAILING MONSTER bumped with an outer foe upon leaving the gates, lacked speed two wide and between horses, tucked to the rail at the three furlong pole, and failed to menace thereafter. RHYME SCHEMES chased four wide and faded. TOP OF THE STREET made little impact. THE RUSH IS ON was outrun. EARLY MUNNY saved ground off of the pace, but weakened after shifting out entering the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHURCHILL DOWNS RACE 4 1 3/8M Turf CR: 99. Allowance Purse 127000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of $24,600 Over Nine Furlongs On The Turf Since March 18 Allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $35,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at one mile and one quarter.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FRIVOLE (FR) leaned outwardly while off a step slow, laid unhurried two wide, tipped five wide in upper stretch, then offered a good kick to drive past the new leader nearing the final sixteenth and drew clear. ELLE EST FORTE pulled two wide and between horses before checking around the first turn, settled into a tracking position soon after, smoothly tipped to the four path entering the lane to take aim on the leaders, ranged up to bid at the furlong grounds, but shifted inwardly while forging an advantage at that juncture, then got outkicked by an outer on charging foe entering the final sixteenth. JOYFUL APPLAUSE pressed two wide, vied around the far turn, dueled in the three path and between horses coming to midstretch, but was herded inwardly while getting outkicked by her outer counterpart at the furlong pole, and held show thereafter. LOVED REIKO bumped an outer rival at the start, saved ground off of the pace, sustained stride after altering off of the rail at the furlong grounds, and gained fourth from between horses late. HAY STACK leaned outwardly while slow away, raced at the rear along the inside while keen behind foes moving through upper stretch for the first time, settled entering the second turn, rallied five wide and outside of foes around the final bend, but fanned seven wide entering the lane and leveled off. SWEETS MAKER set the pace along the inside, vacated the rail while clinging to an advantage entering the lane, but was herded inwardly by outer foes at the furlong grounds while weakening. SUCH SOUNDS was a bit antsy in the starting gate, then took mild contact from rivals on both sides at the start, stalked along the inside, attempted a rail bid in upper stretch, but steadied hard when shut off by inwardly drifting rivals at the furlong grounds, and failed to recover. LA TOURISTA lacked speed while five wide, then three wide around the second turn, attempted to advance four wide around teh far turn, but weakened between horses in upper stretch. CHATON ROUGE was a bit crowded between horses at the start, raced at the rear two wide, then was outrun after taking the final turn in the five path. QUEEN JUDITH was antsy awaiting the start, bumped an inner rival leaving the gates, tracked three wide, pressed approaching the far turn, but weakened between horses turning for home. DIVINELY BOLT transferred contact from an inner rival into an outer foe at the start, raced forwardly between horses, but steadied around the first turn, laid off of the pace three wide thereafter, but weakened. A STEWARDS' INQUIRY REVIEWING THE STRETCH RUN RESULTED IN NO CHANGE TO THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
